Masimo (NASDAQ: MASI) headquartered in Irvine, California, is a fast-growing and award-winning international medical technology and device company with operations spanning the globe. We develop innovative, noninvasive monitoring technologies that save, extend and improve the lives of people of all ages, in all walks of life. These revolutionary technologies are helping to solve "unsolvable" problems that have plagued the healthcare industry, while taking the pain and discomfort out of blood monitoring. For 30 years, innovation has been and will continue to be our passion.

We are looking to recruit the position of:

Technical Services Engineer

Amsterdam, Netherlands

Job Summary:

The Technical Services Engineer is responsible for providing technical support and services, managing customer relationship and service quality, transitioning and on-boarding new customers and solutions, leading technical investigations, and driving solution and technology adoption

This job reports to: Manager, Technical Services.
Department: Technical Service and Field Support


Duties & Responsibilities:

Provide field and remote support for Masimo’s products, solutions and technology including OEM devices
Receive and respond to telephone calls and emails from end users;
Promptly report customer complaints per the requirements defined in Masimo’s Quality System Supports/troubleshoots system problems; including configuring and coordinating with Masimo, vendors or hospital staff (nursing, doctors maintenance, IT and biomedical) on the support of all component items including such items as cables, routers, access points, bridges, and switches;
Initiate repair/replacement of failed and/or defective products;
Performs repairs on customer returned products
Perform periodic Functional Verification, upgrades and unscheduled service calls as needed;
Provide technical support to Masimo Sales Representative during pre-sales activities;
Assist customers in proper use of Masimo products, solutions and technology;
Identify potential Customer training issues and propose solutions;
Follow-up to ensure closure of product and training issues to ensure overall customer satisfaction is achieved;
Convey information from the field regarding product suggestions, improvements and enhancements to Product Marketing;
Implement service sales strategies;
Monitor technical support process and procedures. Initiate changes to optimize the process;
Be able to work with and be knowledgeable of biohazard products and procedures;
Manage and triage escalations for key customers to ensure proper and timely resolution
Advocate for customers by identifying improvement opportunities in services and products quality and performance
Frequent travel with little notice required;
Performs other duties or special projects as requested;
Must be able to lift at least 20kg
Fluent in local language and English is required. Other languages are a plus


Minimum & Preferred Qualifications and Experience:
Three years of related experience in the medical and hospital industry;
Direct Technical experience, ability to communicate with all areas of healthcare industry;
Knowledge of the hospital environment and key personnel within medical care areas;
Intermediate skills in TCP/IP protocol in an Enterprise environment. CCNA or equivalent a plus;
Intermediate skills in routing and switching technology and concepts and network systems troubleshooting skills;
Intermediate skills in Microsoft Windows, VMware, and Linux operating systems;
Must be a self-starter, a "hands-on" individual who enjoys challenge and is and dedicated to getting the job done with minimal support and direction;
Must have excellent verbal and written communication skills;
Strong results orientation, positive "can do" attitude, and a sense of urgency to get things done;
Must have flexibility in reacting to new situations and adaptability for working in a new environment;
Ability to travel both domestically and internationally; eligible to apply for a Passport;
Ability to work on a rotating after-hours on-call schedule;
Ability to work effectively with cross functional teams;
Strengths in organization and working individually and within Team environments;
Field Experience in implementing/troubleshooting medical equipment into the hospital environment;
Must be able to lift at least 20kg;
Fluent in local language and English is required. Other languages a plus


Preferred Qualifications:

Call center experience with a global service provider of manufactured products;
Prior experience in the Biomedical and/or Field Service;
Experience in Medical devices industry preferred;
Experience in regulated industry;


Education:

A Bachelor’s of Science in engineering or biomedical degree is required. Or equivalent related clinical or technical experience in lieu of a BS degree.


Physical requirements/Work Environment
This position primarily works in hospital and hospital-like environments, including, but not limited to, patient rooms, data centers, Biomed shops, etc. It requires frequent sitting, standing, walking, and lifting. Team members must be able to lift up to 20 kg. Daily use of a computer and other computing and digital devices is required. May stand or sit for extended periods when installing, configuring, troubleshooting, and upgrading Masimo products, facilitating meetings or walking in the facilities. Frequent local and domestic travel is necessary, so the ability to operate a motor vehicle and maintain a valid Driver’s license is required. Occasional international travel may be necessary, so the ability to obtain a valid passport may be required.

The physical demands of the position described herein are essential functions of the job and employees must be able to successfully perform these tasks for extended periods. Reasonable accommodations may be made for those individuals with real or perceived disabilities to perform the essential functions of the job described.


